<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,151,1223]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[199,317,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Etymology</emphasis>
. Referring to the preference (Latin: 
<emphasis box="[748,825,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">-philus</emphasis>
) to the genus of their main host plants (
<taxonomicName box="[1309,1419,1056,1079]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1309,1419,1056,1079]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Impatiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Gender: feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,151,1223]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[199,241,1128,1151]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Key</emphasis>
. The multiple-entry key “ 
<taxonomicName box="[548,693,1126,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Impatiophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[548,693,1126,1151]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Impatiophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[712,802,1126,1151]" kingdom="Plantae" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[817,980,1126,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Drosophilidae</taxonomicName>
)” to all species of this genus has been constructed based on a database of morphological characters, and is available from the website “Biological Classification and Identification System (BioCIS: http://biokey.museum.hokudai.ac.jp/Classification/index.jsp)”.
</paragraph>
